  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to evaluate the impact of the enteral nutrition type (untreated
      breast milk, or breast milk processed by the breast-milk bank) on the longitudinal evolution
      of the total content and plasma profile of essential fatty acids (EFA) in a population of
      premature infants.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
